Variable Descriptions

The variable school is a binary variable that states which school the student attends (GP or MS).

The sex variable is a binary variable that lists the sex of the student (M or F).

The age variable is numerical and lists the students age from 15-22.

The address variable is categorical and states whether the student lives in a rural (R) or urban (U) area.

The famsize variable is a categorical variable that states whether the students family is less than or equal 3 (LE3) or greater than 3 (GT3).

Pstatusis a categorical variable that classifies parental cohabitation as living together (T) or living apart (A).

Medu is a categorical variable that lists the students mothers education level on a scale from 0-4. Similarly, the Pedu is a categorical variable that lists the students fathers education level on a scale from 0-4. 0 indicates none, 1 indicates primary education (4th grade), 2 indicates 5th to 9th grade, 3 indicates secondary education, and 4 indicates higher education.

Mjob is a categorical variable that lists the students mothers job. Fjob is similar but refers to the students fathers job. The categories include teacher, health care related, civil services (e.g.administrative or police), at_home, or other.

The variable reason is a categorical variable that lists the reason why the student decided to attend the school. The categories include close to home, school reputation, course preference, or other.
